Fair pricing, honest service, and quality work. That’s exactly what I was looking for over 25 years.. sad but true.

Superb service, great expert repair, very reasonable prices.  The mechanics at Petersen fixed my '93 Saab 900 when no one else in Chicago knew what was wrong with it.

Ian and Tyler were both great:  SO helpful and considerate.  They even took my car to the body shop for a necessary repair and had a loaner car for me to borrow.

I can't say enough great things about Petersen.  These guys love Saabs and are true experts.  I'll never take my car anywhere else!

They are fast, kind, honest and have great people skills! All 4 dudes I interacted with  seemed like genuinely respectable people. Very clean lobby with phone chargers to borrow, nice books to look at and coffee to drink while you wait!

Consistent integrity. Rare in auto mechanics. They are a nostalgic presence that reminds you that business isn't just another economic transaction.

reviews.text: Melinda, Ed, and the entire team at True Performance are truly amazing! Have always had great experiences with them and will continue to come back for any auto body needs I have. They truly set the highest of standards for any body shop in central ohio. They are the best!

These folks are true professionals. I had the whole rear quarter of my 2019 XC60 smashed in after 8,000 miles, and they meticulously rebuilt the car (using genuine parts) over 2 months. I’m writing now because 40,000 miles later the car remains a high functioning vehicle with no hidden issues. Don’t hesitate to use these guys should you ever find yourself in the unfortunate circumstance I did.

We have been customers of True Performance for almost twenty years and they continue to impress and surprise.

Unfortunately, our latest visit to Randall and his team was due to my wife's car being involved in a hit & skip while she was inside our local grocery store.

True Performance quickly scheduled an appointment and I had the opportunity to meet with Rob Williams.  He evaluated the car thoroughly and even took the time to clean a few areas to remove plastic residue left from the other vehicle.  He provided quotes for both the work from the accident and some additional work that I wanted to perform if the budget allowed.

Rob worked directly with our insurance company to ensure proper repairs would be made and covered under our policy.  He also made professional recommendations for some rust repair that was discovered once the body panels were removed.

During the course of the work being performed, our vehicle was subject to some additional damage for which True Performance took full responsibility.  They were honest, up front, and explained how they were going to make it right while providing a rental car and updated timeline for repairs.  I received a call from the owner himself apologizing for the situation.  I respect when someone takes responsibility for their actions and does their best to make things right.

Regrettably, we were unable to perform the additional work I asked to be quoted due to budgetary constraints, so it was a surprise to us when we picked up the car to find that Randall made the decision to perform that work free of charge.

As usual, we were thrilled with the quality of the work performed which has been the primary reason for bringing our vehicles here for the last two decades.  Frankly, we had debated trading the car in for something newer, but after seeing the finished product we knew we would be keeping it in the family for years to come.

I have nothing but respect for the entire team at True Performance and thank them for their professionalism and commitment to quality.  Keep up the great work!

True Performance is gold standard of collision repair centers.  True Performance repaired rear end damage after my Mercedes was in an accident last month.  When the repairs were complete, it looked as good as (if not better than) the day I purchased it brand new.  Truly exceptional.  Just last week, another person hit my vehicle.  At the accident scene, I told the police officer that I have a good collision repair place & without hesitation he said, “I hope it’s True Performance.”  Knowing that True Performance will take exceptional care of my vehicle from start to finish, puts me at ease.  In addition to their outstanding repair expertise, the team at True Performance is very kind, friendly, punctual & knowledgeable.  I sincerely hope that I’m never in an accident again, but if so, True Performance is where I would go.  Thank you for everything.
There is not a better body shop in Columbus.   From the body shop technicians to the owners, the professionalism and care taken of your car is number 1 in my book.

reviews.text:
IMO There is no comparable shop to Blue Chip.

The quality of care and maintenance for my (and every) vehicle in their hands is absolutely paramount.
The attention to detail is exemplary, and I would trust no other shop (Porsche dealer included) in the maintenance and any work on my car.

BlueChip was an absolute gem in assisting us with the repair and sale of my late father's 1980 Porsche 911 SC. From the very beginning, the owner (Stover) impressed us with his exceptional expertise and passion for luxury cars, which made the entire selling process incredibly smooth and efficient. He breathed new life into my dad's vehicle after it had been sitting in the garage for decades, and the attention to detail in showcasing its excellence was truly commendable.

Working with Stover and his team was a delight, and his meticulous guidance and valuable insights proved his unmatched understanding of high-end vehicles. I highly recommend BlueChip for anyone looking to sell their cherished automobiles. Stover's professionalism, expertise, and genuine love for expensive cars make his shop stand out from the rest. If you need mechanic work or wish to sell luxury vehicles, this is the place to go.

Seeing my dad's Porsche in its finest condition was a heartwarming experience. I know he would have been immensely proud of its final state. Thank you, BlueChip, for providing outstanding service and finding a deserving new home for my father's beloved Porsche!

While nearing the end of our month long stay in Breckenridge Colorado, I noticed an oil smell coming from the engine bay of my Lotus Evora. A seal on the transmission had come loose and made a big mess. Just days away from the planned return drive to Austin Texas, I became very concerned. The Local Lotus club recommended Blue Chip and to have Ryan Chapman repair my car. I called Blue Chip and shared my concern  with James, the shop manager. I let James know that I was planning to go home in a few days. Well, Ryan and James didn't let me down. The repair was performed in time to keep me on schedule for my return to Texas. The car was also thoroughly cleaned from the inside and out. Blue Chip staff are caring and take pride in their work. I can't tell you how much I appreciate them. I frequent Colorado and I will keep Blue Chip on speed dial.

September 29th, 2022

Blue Chip, has done it again. During a our recent stay in Colorado, our Lotus Elise R S3 had a mystery problem causing the engine to die. The car was not drivable, so we had it towed to blue Chip from Breckinridge. The shop owner, Stover stayed available after hours to coordinate the towing and get the car inside the shop. Unfortunately, the timing of the breakdown wasn't great, we needed to drive back to Austin, Texas on October 1st. Blue Chip understood our situation and even though they had many clients on the books, they put in the extra time to figure out the problem and get us on the road home.  I'm very impressed and wish I could pack their shop up in the trunk of the car and take them all back to Texas. The shop manager, Joe, deserves praise as he kept me well informed through the whole process. The technician, Ryan Chapman, was very impressive as he had it all figured out so quickly. Lastly, the car was returned to me cleaner than I have ever seen it.  I highly recommend Blue Chip Denver.

I bought a down-and-out 996 that Blue Chip breathed new life in to. Stover  and Marco run a best-in-class shop and always makes me feel like their best client (and I know they have a lot of better clients). Chance is a Porsche expert and cares deeply about the cars that he works on. Blue Chip brings expert service and transparency to everything they do. And its a really rad place to hang out while you wait. Below is before/after... lots more was done than can be seen.

Chance and the crew down there at Blue Chip went above and beyond for me. I had them do some work on my Cayman. It sits very low and they were able to align it still. They got it all done in short notice so the car would be ready for a weekend event I had. They will be the only place I go moving forward.

reviews.text: I'm a long time customer and I can't get a return call after months of calling emailing and texting not even the courtesy of a simple phone call had to go with a shop that cares about its clients
Impressive museum and showcase for MBZ classic autos.  Change of vehicles regularly.  Gary is a great guy to work with if you need parts.  Parts are expensive but are OEM.
1 of 2 Classic centers in the world, the other being in Germany. Truly impressive showroom with some of the best vehicles ever built by Mercedes-Benz

Very poor service. First of all, everything the classic center has, you can just get from any regular Mercedes dealership, and often cheaper too. I was looking at a $120 part offered from another Benz dealer for $90. But I figured being a classic car guy I want to support the classic center. So I call them up to ask, and he has they can do 20% off MSRP. I figure $96 is negligibly more than $90, plus classic center advertises free shipping on order over $49, so I say sure. Then he rings me up at $132. How come I cay. He goes 120 - 10% off + shipping and tax. SO I say you said $20% off and supposed to be free shipping. And he says "no, it's UP TO 20% off and if I give you a discount then you don't get free shipping". Okay...... I go for it anyway. Again, want to support the classic center. And I say I'll just come pick it up in person.

Over there...nice place. But no humans to be found. Couple guys sitting in some office, I have to shout to get their attention. They bring the part. Fine. I go out open my hood to check and compare that part is right. While at it I notice I have a cracked little piece of vacuum hose. Just an inch piece. SO I go back and ask if they could just cut me an inch of hose from the shop (shop is right there). And guy goes "no, we sell that".

So in the end ... what's the difference buy from regular dealer vs classic center. Classic center might say "the service". But what service did I get here?

Not worth my business. Not worth my drive. Just not worth it.
Absolutely amazing!

reviews.text: These guys are the real deal. Great selection of tires. Knowledgeable staff. Decent prices. I had need to make an insurance claim and they already had open lines of communication with my insurance co. And my rental car was deeply discounted.

They did a good job. The guy was a little grumpy and it took longer than estimated, but they got it right. I’ve had problems with other services (Tacoma Toyota always pulls to the right) but these people got it perfect.

These guys are awesome! My alignment was off for a few days and pulling slightly to the left but as I was coming off the Bay Bridge the other day I started hearing a clunking noise and suddenly the steering wheel was pulling _hard_ all the way to the left. I was fighting it just to go straight. Since All Tire is a few blocks from where I work I dropped by there around 1:00 in the afternoon. They immediately knew what the problem was and showed me what was going on. Apparently it's a fairly common thing with the Dodge vans of that era.

Despite them having every bay full and several more alignments to be done, they said they would try to get me in on very short notice because I needed to Sacramento after work. Otherwise, I would have been stranded in the city. They called me about 15 minutes before closing and they got it done. The van is driving straight again! When a mechanic saves the day like this on short notice, always tip them some extra cash (I did)! 🙏👏💪🖖

Al and his team are the best. Honest people, fair price and excellent, fast work! They did an awesome job with my Prius C. I got a whole set of wheels and tires from them for a good price, all the parts came in within the promised time and the service was performed fast and well. Couldn’t be happier with my new good looking Prius! I highly recommend this place! Great customer service as well! Thanks Al!

These guys come through for me all the time.

Ben and his crew are very knowledgeable.

I recommend All Tire if you need work done on you vehicle.

organization.description: a euro american auto repairs & tire center has been maintaining and repairing vehicles in astoria since 1988. we have a dedicated team of technicians with a combined experience of over 60 years specializing in foreign and domestic vehicle services.
